cs.LG, cs.CL, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE 

The paper discusses the use of Long Short-term Memory (LSTM) recurrent neural networks for generating complex sequences with long-range structure. This topic falls under the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG) as well as natural language processing (cs.CL) and computer vision (cs.CV) since the approach is demonstrated for both text and online handwriting. Additionally, the paper involves the use of neural networks for prediction and generation, which falls under the sub-categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE).
